 the flight due to the thunderstorms, and noted that this was standard procedure during inclement weather.\nUS-based airline pilot Patrick Smith remarked that the plane could have crashed for many reasons. \"Had the plane encountered extreme turbulence, or had it suffered a powerful lightning strike that knocked out instruments while penetrating strong turbulence, then structural failure or loss of control, followed by an in-flight breakup, are possible causes.\""}
